      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Distinct weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on west, north and east facing slopes. <br/> <br/> Outgoing longwave radiation during the night will be good over a wide area. Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise as the day progresses to rapid and thorough wetting of the snowpack. This applies especially on steep sunny slopes below approximately 2400 m."
      },
